Based on the search results, here are a few ways to create a curve line in CSS:

**Method 1: Using CSS Borders**

You can create a curved line using CSS borders. Here's an example:
```
.curve {
  width: 100px;
  height: 50px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 2px solid #000;
}
```
This will create a curved line with a radius of 50% of the element.

**Method 2 Using CSS Gradients**

You can also use CSS gradients to create a curved line. Here's an example:
```
.curve {
  width: 100px;
  height: 50px;
  background: radial-gradient(farthest-corner at 50% 50%, #000 50%, transparent 50%);
}
```
This will create a curved line with a gradient effect.

**Method 3: Using SVG**

You can use SVG to create a curved line. Here's an example:
```
<svg width="100" height="50">
  <path d="M10,20 C20,40 30,80 40,60" stroke="#000" fill="none" />
</svg>
```
This will create a curved line using the `path` element in SVG.

**Method 4: Using CSS Bezier Curves**

You can use CSS Bezier curves to create a curved line. Here's an example:
```
.curve {
  width: 100px;
  height: 50px;
  border: 2px solid #000;
  border-radius: 50% 50% 50% 50%/70% 70% 70% 70%;
}
```
This will create a curved line using the `border-radius` property with Bezier curve values.

These are just a few examples of how you can create a curve line in CSS. You can experiment with different methods and properties to create the curve line that suits your needs.

